<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: The 'inherit' keyword value is allowed in a list of identifiers.</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transitions/#the-transition-property-property-" />
        <meta name="flags" content="animated dom" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The 'inherit' keyword value is allowed in a list of identifiers." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #parent
            {
                transition-property: opacity;
            }
            #testDiv
            {
                background-color: blue;
                height: 50px;
                left: 0%;
                opacity: 0;
                position: relative;
                transition-property: left, inherit;
                transition-duration: 5s, 5s;
                transition-timing-function: linear, linear;
                width: 50px;
            }
        </style>
        <script type="text/javascript">
            function startTest()
            {
                document.body.offsetWidth;
                var element1 = document.getElementById("testDiv"); 
                element1.style["left"] = "90%";
                element1.style["opacity"] = "1";
            }
        </script>
    </head>
    <body onload="startTest()">
        <p>Test passes if the blue block changes from a light to darker shade of blue while moving from left to right across the page.</p>
        <div id="parent">
            <div id="testDiv"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
